1.title: Return of the Living Stash
1.plot: Kevin Smith and the guys discuss how "The Walking Dead" started out as a comic book and became a cultural phenomenon.

2.title: Nightmare on Broad Street
2.plot: Legendary horror icon Robert Englund, aka Freddy Krueger, personally delivers a birthday present to Ming.

3.title: Hail to the King
3.plot: The Stash & Red Bank cosplayers celebrate the Centennial of the late, great Jack Kirby, one of the greatest innovators in comic book history.

4.title: Method Man's Mego
4.plot: Influential actor and rapper Method Man talks to the guys about his extensive comic book collection. Starsky & Hutch gear takes over The Stash.

5.title: Stash Bash
5.plot: Jay & Silent Bob cosplayers take over the streets of Red Bank as the Comic Book Men attempt to make history by setting a Guinness World Record.

6.title: In a Galaxy Very Nearby
6.plot: Walt tries to purchase rare and interesting Star Wars items for the store.

7.title: Ode to Clerks
7.plot: Kevin Smith and the guys attend a premiere screening of Ode to Clerks, a film about themselves and how Clerks came to be.

8.title: Canine Crusaders
8.plot: Batman actor Burt Ward talks about his time as the Caped Crusader and judges a canine cosplay contest.

9.title: Power Man vs. Counter Man
9.plot: Walt negotiates with Luke Cage actor Mike Colter.

10.title: Troma-tized
10.plot: What does it take to be in a Troma film? The staff endure a grueling audition to see if they have it.

11.title: A Pez-tacular Mystery
11.plot: The Stash staff research if Walt actually owns a valuable piece of Pez history by visiting the Pez Museum.

12.title: The Mightiest of Mortals
12.plot: Walt decides that he must meet the "Mighty Mortal" when he learns that Ming knows actor Michael Gray from Shazam.

13.title: Pop Goes the Stash
13.plot: Kevin Smith joins the Stash staff to attend the grand opening of Funko's new headquarters.

1.title: Junk
1.plot: Walt challenges his staff to a flea market sales competition.

2.title: Life After Clerks
2.plot: Kevin comes to town for a friendly game of street hockey. And hurricane Jason Mewes blows through the Stash.

3.title: Commercial
3.plot: Bryan directs the Secret Stash's first commercial. Three customers with rare books to sell show up: one with a box of valuable comics her garbage-collector husband found on the curb; a second with a stack of classic Fireside Books (some of the first "trade paperback" comic collections published); and the third with his grandmother's comic collection potentially worth $750,000. Another young lady - a struggling artist with a wild hairdo - shows up to sell off her collector's edition Megatron figure.

4.title: Zombies
4.plot: Ming plans a sales promotion around zombies.

5.title: Con Gone Wrong
5.plot: Walt and the guys take a road trip to a convention in the area. After a major setback, the guys end up finding a literal treasure in the trash.

6.title: Ink
6.plot: Ming dares Walt, Bryan and Mike to get tattoos, but will each of the Comic Book Men go through with it?

1.title: Stash Bashes
1.plot: Walt and the guys decide to throw a birthday party at the Stash. One customer comes in with a larger-than-life Darth Vader helmet.

2.title: My Big Fat Geek Wedding
2.plot: The guys attend a local auction; bad result from mixing comic books and cigars.

3.title: Ghostbusting at the Stash
3.plot: The guys hunt for the Jersey Devil. One customer tries to sell his Thundercat figures and finds that loose items aren't always popular.

4.title: Ming in Charge
4.plot: When Walt and Mike fall ill, Ming must run Stash by himself; first issues of Iron Man and Daredevil.

5.title: The Sidewalk Stash
5.plot: Ming arranges for the Stash to join in on the local sidewalk sale; Walt sells some early "Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles' comics.

6.title: The Running Dead
6.plot: Mike and Ming participate in a 5K zombie run for Kevin's charity. Walt buys an unusual item containing signatures from the 1966 Batman TV show.

7.title: Tough Sh*T
7.plot: Kevin visits the Stash for a book signing; Jay acts as security; a customer brings in original artwork.

8.title: Stan the Man
8.plot: The guys prepare for a visit from Stan Lee; Walt has a chance to buy a valuable comic book.

9.title: The Clash at the Stash
9.plot: Walt haggles to see a costumed MMA fight.

10.title: Super Hoagie
10.plot: The guys make sandwiches for the Stash.

11.title: Stash-teroids
11.plot: Arcade history rolls into the Stash.

12.title: Con Men
12.plot: The Stash auctions off a huge collection.

13.title: Stash Wars
13.plot: Walt puts a game system on consignment.

14.title: Cryptozoic Men
14.plot: The guys create their own comic book.

15.title: Comic Charades
15.plot: On a slow day, the guys play charades.

16.title: Giant-Sized Anniversary
16.plot: Ming plans a surprise for Walt.

1.title: The Incredible Bulk
1.plot: The Hulk gives Bryan a fitness lesson.

2.title: To the Bat Cave
2.plot: A customer shows off his "bat cave."

3.title: Super Friends
3.plot: The guys ask artist George Perez to help rebuild Mike's destroyed collection. A customer sells his set of vintage interactive comic books.

4.title: U.S.S. Ming
4.plot: Ming's interest is piqued when he has a chance to buy an oversized toy from the '80s. A customer needs help taking his wife out on the perfect date.

5.title: Pity the Fools
5.plot: A superfan sells his Mr. T backyard water game and inspires Ming to have some cool fun on a hot day. Walt puts the shop's street cred on the line.

6.title: Walt's Big Gamble
6.plot: Walt decides the team should check out a storage locker auction.

7.title: Dukes of Jersey
7.plot: The boys take a ride on the General Lee.

8.title: Cryptozoic Launch
8.plot: The shop gets more customers and the shop's comic gets launched at a comic con with a surprise guest.

9.title: Superman's 75th
9.plot: The guys throw a 75th birthday party for the Man of Steel.

10.title: Uhura's Uhura
10.plot: Nichelle Nichols pays the Stash a visit, looking for an Uhura Mego doll from the '70s. An X-Men fan buys the first appearance of the Phoenix.

11.title: Pinheads
11.plot: "Pinheads" Walt's recent purchase of a Batman bowling ball inspires him to make a bowling team. An ill-conceived action figure makes its way to the Stash. AMC Original.

12.title: Trivia Chew-Off
12.plot: "Trivia Chew-Off" A bored Walt decides to quiz the guys on comic book trivia, where a wrong answer lands them a gumball. A customer sells his Hellboy prop replica. AMC Original.

13.title: The Esposito Collection
13.plot: The Stash helps auction off the work of legendary comic book inker, Mike Esposito. Walt buys the epitome of cool in the form of a paper doll.

14.title: Batcycle on Broad
14.plot: The guys have a chance to purchase a replica of the '66 Batcycle. A customer sells his collection of Marvel fan magazines from the '70s.

15.title: Certified Guaranty
15.plot: A college hopeful goes to the Stash to appraise his collection and learns the value of comic book grading. Walt buys Wayne Gretzky memorabilia.

16.title: Knights of the Stash
16.plot: Jason Mewes invites the guys to a Renaissance fair for medieval revelry. A customer brings in one of the most valuable items the Stash has ever seen.

1.title: Heir Apparent
1.plot: Kevin Smith sends his daughter Harley to the Stash to learn how to be a clerk. A customer sells his rare and unusual Rocky action figures.

2.title: Walt's Treehouse
2.plot: The comic book men come a cross very important marble store a cool book with some signatures.

3.title: Stand Up Guys
3.plot: Walt challenges the guys to perform stand up comedy at the Stash. A collector brings in key Marvel comics from the 1960s.

4.title: Super Baby
4.plot: The guys agree to help out a friend and babysit her daughter for the afternoon. An Indiana Jones superfan tries to sell rare items from the films.

5.title: BronyCon
5.plot: The men go to attend BronyCon to scout out new ideas for merchandise to sell at the store, while also competing in the cosplay contest.

6.title: Bat Prints
6.plot: Walt considers buying hand and foot prints of Adam West and Burt Ward from the Batman TV show. A customer sells a rare set of Star Wars comic strips.

7.title: Turtle Time
7.plot: Kevin Eastman, co-creator of the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, brings in his earliest sketches of the turtles to the Stash.

8.title: Stashbusters
8.plot: With the help of Ernie Hudson, the guys transform an ice cream truck into a mobile comic store.

9.title: Dragging Rights
9.plot: Adam West visits and a drag race between the Batmobile and the Black Beauty ignites. A customer sells the 1st comic appearance of Rocket Raccoon.

10.title: Mr. Adams
10.plot: Comic legends, artist Neal Adams and writer Denny O'Neil, drop by the Stash. The guys look at a pristine set of 50-year-old Batman night lights.

11.title: My Favorite Munster
11.plot: Butch Patrick stops by the Stash; a never officially rare Star Wars action figure of Boba Fett.

12.title: Secret Stashley
12.plot: Kevin's assistant Ashley brings her feminine wiles to the Stash and learns about comic book retail. A pair of pro wrestlers wants to sell their comic.

13.title: Sucka M.C.
13.plot: Hip hop legend Darryl McDaniels of Run DMC brings his new comic in to the Stash. The guys look at a classic Marvel Silver Age #1 issue.

14.title: Falcon for Sale
14.plot: Star Wars legend Billy Dee Williams drops by the Stash to win the Millennium Falcon the same way Lando lost it - in a high stakes card game.

15.title: KISS My Stash
15.plot: The boys rock out at a KISS concert and Walt lives out his childhood dream of meeting Gene Simmons. Ming considers buying an arcade cabinet.

16.title: Jay Invades
16.plot: Jason Mewes drops by the Stash to hang out and play clerk. Walt looks to acquire a mysterious recreation of some iconic comic book art.

1.title: Wookiee Fever
1.plot: Chewbacca himself, Peter Mayhew, judges a wookiee call contest at the Stash. One of the hottest comic books of the '90s lands on the counter.

2.title: Holy Zap Copter!
2.plot: Mike takes flight in the Batcopter to celebrate 15 years at the Secret Stash. The boys look at one of the hottest books of the '90s.

3.title: Captain and the Clerk
3.plot: Kevin meets with the original captain of Starfleet, William Shatner, to talk comics. Walt drools over a Mego doll with unique packaging.

4.title: Bryan Gets Bit
4.plot: The guys help Bryan take a dip into the icy waters of collecting by visiting a "JAWS museum." A roll of super-powered toilet paper comes through.

5.title: Stash-pocalypse
5.plot: A hot zombie comic prompts the guys to reconsider their apocalyptic preparations. An eccentric collector comes seeking Walt's help.

6.title: Stan Saves!
6.plot: Stan Lee drops by the Stash and helps the guys with a customer experiencing a comics crisis. A customer buys a classic issue of Fantastic Four.

7.title: Making Clay
7.plot: Walt and Bryan decide to make a claymation video and audition fellow Stash employees, along with friends, to find the best voices.

8.title: Royal Romita
8.plot: John Romita Jr, a comic book legend, visits the Stash and the crew talks him into drawing an original art work for their wall.

9.title: Suburban Cowboys
9.plot: An old pal inspires the gang to don their cowboy hats and journey back to the old Wild West. A customer comes in seeking an iconic '80s comic.

10.title: Tell 'Em Jim Lee
10.plot: Superstar artist Jim Lee guests on the podcast and regales the guys with tales of comic-dom. A comic book brings wedding bells to the Stash.

11.title: Insta-Ming
11.plot: Ming gets a selfie stick and tries to go viral filming behind-the-scenes looks at the Stash. Walt takes a look at bootleg toys of an '80s blockbuster.

12.title: Baby Jay
12.plot: Jason Mewes brings his baby daughter to the Stash so she can meet the guys. A customer sells a collection of comic book Slurpee cups.

13.title: Hometown Heroes
13.plot: Phoenix Jones, a real-life superhero, visits the Stash and patrols Red Bank with the guys. Walt reminisces about an iconic Batman playset.

1.title: Bucket List
1.plot: Walt & the boys go on a trip to cross off a bucket-list item: being in the presence of Action Comics #1. Four key Spider-Man issues come to the Stash.

2.title: Mistress of the Stash
2.plot: The Stash sponsors a blood drive at the shop with the help of horror queen Elvira; the boys discuss the joys of "Mystery Science Theater 3000."

3.title: Pac-Ming
3.plot: When a vintage 1980s Pac-Man game lands on the counter, Ming prepares for battle; a rare Beatles board game excites the guys

4.title: KITT and Caboodle
4.plot: One of TV's most iconic cars, KITT from Knight Rider, pulls up to the Stash. Items include a rare Green Arrow Mego, and Archie Bunker's grandson.

5.title: Bionic Customer
5.plot: Walt is speechless when The Bionic Woman herself, Lindsay Wagner, stops in to buy a Silver Surfer item. Ghostbusters and Jem toys spark some banter.

6.title: Joust-a-Bouts
6.plot: Things get medieval when Ming and a customer joust over the price of Batman #111. Wolverine shows up as the largest statue to ever enter the Stash.

7.title: Wurst Episode Ever
7.plot: Kevin and Harley come to town for the Yoga Hosers premiere, and Ming gets transformed into the lead villain by a special-effects makeup legend.

8.title: Stash Troopers
8.plot: Members of the 501st Legion of Storm Troopers invade the Stash looking for new recruits. Lives are at stake over the fate of a vintage Ewok playset.

9.title: Karate Kustomer
9.plot: Ralph Macchio stops by looking for a rare Karate Kid playset, and Ming gets a lesson he'll never forget. Walt flips over a pricey Mechagodzilla.

10.title: Bats Ahoy!
10.plot: The Batboat docks in Red Bank, and the boys prepare for an adventure at sea. Batman's first appearance lands on the counter of the Secret Stash.

11.title: Return of the Mewes
11.plot: Jason Mewes hangs with the boys and inserts himself into transactions involving a Deadshot statue and a vintage Death Star Space Station.

12.title: Daughter of the Demon
12.plot: Actress Katrina Law from Arrow drops by to pick up a copy of Batman #232. Old school items involving Popeye, Dynomutt, and Pogs get some love.

13.title: Rock 'Em Sock 'Em Stash
13.plot: Walt steps into the ring with a customer over an original Rock 'Em Sock 'Em Robots game. A rare piece of original Sal Buscema art comes in.

14.title: Marky Ramone-Bot
14.plot: Ramones drummer Marky Ramone shows off his artwork and bonds with Walt over old school robots. A King Kong item bring the boys back to 1975.

15.title: The Amazing Walter
15.plot: A Kreskin ESP game reveals Walt's secret powers of cognition. Items inspire discussions about Mork from Ork and Dick Tracy's Rogues' Gallery.

16.title: Reverse Stash
16.plot: The boys get a visit from Tom Cavanagh who plays Reverse Flash on The Flash TV series. Walt sniffs out a Golden Age classic with Human Torch #2.

imdb.title: Comic Book Men
plot: An unscripted series set in Smith's iconic comic shop Jay and Silent Bob's Secret Stash and captures the world of the neighborhood comic book store and fanboy culture.::AMC Publicity
